Package: easieRnmt
Title: EasyNMT for R
Version: 0.0.5
Authors@R: 
    person("Daniel", "Thiele", , "daniel.thiele@fu-berlin.de", role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-0324-4943"))
Description: R wrapper around the Python library 'EasyNMT' <https://github.com/UKPLab/EasyNMT>, enabling easy-to-use, local, reproducible machine translation. The package takes care of tokenization, pre-processing, and language detection using 'fastText' from R. Python backend and installation of PyTorch is handled by 'reticulate' and 'uv'. Supports translation between multiple language pairs. 
License: GPL (>= 3)
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
URL: https://github.com/thieled/easieRnmt
BugReports: https://github.com/thieled/easieRnmt/issues
SystemRequirements: A C++11 capable compiler (g++ >= 4.7.2, clang >= 3.3).
  On Windows, Rtools (latest version) must be installed and on PATH.
Imports: 
    cli,
    data.table,
